cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper focuses on image retrieval tasks and proposes a novel network architecture for cross-modal zero-shot hashing. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with multiple modalities (image and text) and proposes a method to align them in a semantically rich attribute space. 
3. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper addresses the problem of cross-modal retrieval and proposes a method to generate hash codes for image and text. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for zero-shot hashing and uses attribute information to guide the generation of hash codes. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with text-based image retrieval and proposes a method to align text and image data in a semantically rich attribute space.
